<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870109-0077 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Inertia Dynamics Corp.</HL><DD> 01/09/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> TRIM </IN><TEXT>   INERTIA DYNAMICS CORP., Phoenix, Ariz., said it rescheduled its annual meeting to March 18 because of its recently announced joint venture with Ryobi Ltd. of Tokyo. The maker of gasoline-powered weed trimmers had initially set its annual meeting for Jan. 20. Holders of record Feb. 2 will be eligible to vote at the meeting. As previously reported, Ryobi, a maker of electric-powered tools, purchased about 34% of Inertia common for about $12 million. The companies agreed to form a venture to make in the U.S. certain electric tools now produced and under development by Ryobi in Japan. </TEXT></DOC>